description.plain:
“Takeaway” is a collaboration between American DJ and production duo The Chainsmokers and American musician Illenium, featuring Lennon Stella as a vocalist.

The song name was accidentally revealed by The Chainsmokers through an Instagram story in February 2018.

The original snippet of the song, with Sorana having the female vocals, was played live at Ultra Miami 2019 during the closing performance from the Chainsmokers, and Illenium was brought on stage to help debut it live. However the finalised and extended version played later at Ultra Europe 2019 replaced Sorana with Lennon Stella, who will be supporting The Chainsmokers on their upcoming World War Joy tour.

On July 17, the track, and its subsequent music video, was teased.

annotations:
We were dancing without moving
 All my friends were leaving me behind
 I didn’t wanna catch a feeling
 But there was something in that flashing light

In the music video to this song you see the seasons come and go. So it is years going by after they first met and took the polaroid. But both of them are frequently thinking about each other. And they feel like they’ve seen the other one numerous times, but only for a blink of an eye. It’s also shown that they almost bump into each other a few times but manage to miss one another by seconds.
In the end of the music video the both of them in fact run into each other and immediately recognize the other person. They both have kids with another partner. The kids start playing together but the two of them just keep looking at each other. It remains open if they are both single parents or if they both have their own lives with a different partner. So in the end of the video it’s unclear whether they will get together or not.

Let me tell you how it happened
 I wasn’t looking for someone that night
 No, I was never a believer
 That you could fall in love at the first sight

The protagonists are on a party. He’s saying that he doesn’t believe in love at first sight. However, before he knew it, it was happening to him. He saw that girl and took a polaroid of her. And in that moment he fell for her.

An instant camera is a type of camera which creates chemically developed prints shortly after a picture is taken.

The cameras, and the pictures they develop are better known as ‘polaroids’ as a result of the Polaroid Corporation which dominated the instant camera market for many decades since being founded in 1937.

description.plain:
In “Kissing Other People,” Lennon Stella explores the themes of moving on after a breakup. She asks herself how she knows she is over her ex, and answer the question too: if you’re able to kiss other people without guilt, then you’ve moved on.

Stella wrote the song at a writing camp in Mexico, after having a conversation with Carolina Ailin about “feeling like I was at a place where I could kiss someone else and not feel sorry about it.”

The song is the first single off her debut album. She first teased the song in an Instagram post, before announcing her 2020 European tour.

description.plain:
‘Pretty Boy’ is about someone Stella meets and believes is ironically deserving of more than the title of just a pretty boy.

This song is a standout track on the album for its partial alternative inspired elements that leave one feeling like their midnight driving down a highway in the middle of a desert. Although a beautiful song that definitely could not be more perfectly crafted,  there is a sense of emptiness in the echos of its sounds that represent the unknown depths to Stella’s said pretty boy that she paints as a mysterious beauty throughout the song.

annotations: Is that why you build Potemkin villages to hide?

‘Potemkin villages’ is a term used to describe any sort of construct that is deceptive to those on the outside, as it creates a facade making itself appear better to the outer world without any sort of correlation to its state inside.

This metaphor is relevant as Stella addresses that although the person she is singing about is quite the ‘Pretty Boy’ there is unknown depths to him she has yet to discover that leave her indefinitely curious about the ways in which his external presentation can overshadow what he keeps hidden inside.

description.plain:
The first ballad of the album, Lennon strips ‘Older Than I Am’ down to bare an honest piece of her heart and soul as a young adult with an abundance of responsibilities.

An older sister, an actress, a musician… the list goes on of titles that encapsulate who Lennon is as a person and with these and many others come responsibilities that together can take a large toll on somebody fresh out of their teenage years.  At only 20 years old, Stella sings so soulfully the ways in which she has matured so quickly and adapted to large emotionally and physically draining lifestyles, and sometimes wishes there was a way she could feel the bliss of being free from the things she’s currently knee-deep in.

Sometimes, I wish I could do something stupid
 Be kinda reckless while I can
 Say I don’t give a damn
 But I’m older than I am
Lennon wishes that she could just be a kid and make mistakes, but she can’t because she spent her childhood in the limelight. She is forced to act older and more mature than she is because of this.
